edicine with joseph l goldstein in  for describing the regulation of cholesterol metabolism contents  education and early life  career and research  awards and honors  bibliography  references education and early lifeedit brown was born in brooklyn new york the son of evelyn a homemaker and harvey brown a textile salesman graduated from cheltenham high school wyncote pa brown graduated from the university of pennsylvania in  and received his md from the university of pennsylvania school of medicine in  career and researchedit moving to the university of texas health science center in dallas now the ut southwestern medical center brown and colleague joseph l goldstein researched cholesterol metabolism and discovered that human cells have lowdensity lipoprotein ldl receptors that extract cholesterol from the bloodstream the lack of sufficient ldl receptors is implicated in familial hypercholesterolemia which predisposes heavily for cholesterolrelated diseases in addition to explaining the underlying pathology of this disease their work uncovered a fundamental aspect of cell biology  receptormediated endocytosis their findings led to the development of statin drugs the cholesterollowering compounds that today are used by  million americans and are the most widely prescribed medications in the united states their discoveries are improving more lives every year both in the united states and around the worldneeds citation new federal cholesterol guidelines will triple the number of americans taking statin drugs to lower their cholesterol reducing the risk of heart disease and stroke for countless people following these important advances their team of dedicated researchers elucidated the role of lipid modification of proteins protein prenylation in cancer in  he was awarded the louisa gross horwitz prize from columbia university together with joseph l goldstein corecipient of  nobel prize in physiology or medicine in  brown received national medal of science for his contributions to the world of medicine in  their trainees xiaodong wang and michael briggs purified the sterol regulatory element binding proteins srebps since  drs brown goldstein and their colleagues have described the unexpectedly complex machinery by which cells maintain the necessary levels of fats and cholesterol in the face of varying environmental circumstances dr brown holds the w a monty moncrief distinguished chair in cholesterol and arteriosclerosis research is a regental professor of the university of texas holds the paul j thomas chair in medicine and is a member of the board of scientific directors at the scripps research institute frequently mentioned as a candidate for nationallyprominent positions in scientific administration dr brown like his colleague joseph l goldstein elects to continue handson involvement with research leading a research team that typically includes a dozen doctoral and postdoctoral trainees he and his colleague are among the most highly cited scientists in the world brown is also on the prestigious prix galien usa committee that recognizes the technical scientific and clinical research skills necessary to develop innovative medicines the inauguration of the prix galien in the us the equivalent of the nobel prize in this field was in september  and the winners were selected by a preeminent scientific and learned committee that included  nobel laureates of which brown was one awards and honorsedit brown has won numerous awards and honors including   keynote speaker at the congress of future medical leaders   stadtman distinguished scientist award american society for biochemistry and molecular biology   builders of science award researchamerica   woodrow wilson award for public service   herbert tabor award american society for biochemistry and molecular biology   albany medical center prize   kober medal association of american physicians   warren alpert foundation prize harvard medical school   elected a foreign member of the royal society formemrs   national medal of science   nobel prize for physiology and medicine   albert lasker award for basic medical research   william allan award american society of human genetics   louisa gross horwitz prize   gairdner foundation international award   elected member of the national academy of sciences    lounsbery award us national academy of sciences   passano award johns hopkins university   pfizer award in enzyme chemistry american chemical society   heinrich wieland prize bibliographyedit brown ms goldstein jl jul  expression of the familial hypercholesterolemia gene in heterozygotes mechanism for a dominant disorder in man science   – pmid  doiscience  brown ms goldstein jl nov  regulation of the activity of the low density lipoprotein receptor in human fibroblasts cell   – pmid  doi  goldstein jl basu sk brunschede gy brown ms jan  release of low density lipoprotein from its cell surface receptor by sulfated glycosaminoglycans cell   – pmid  doi  brown ms goldstein jl jan  receptormediated control of cholesterol metabolism science   – pmid  doiscience  goldstein jl sobhani mk faust jr brown ms oct  heterozygous familial hypercholesterolemia failure of normal allele to compensate for mutant allele at a regulated genetic locus cell   – pmid  doi  brown ms goldstein jl dec  analysis of a mutant strain of human fibroblasts with a defect in the internalization of receptorbound low density lipoprotein cell   pt  – pmid  doi  anderson rg brown ms goldstein jl mar  role of the coated endocytic vesicle in the uptake of receptorbound low density lipoprotein in human fibroblasts cell   – pmid  doi  goldstein jl brown ms stone nj nov  genetics of the ldl receptor evidence that the mutations affecting binding and internalization are allelic cell   – pmid  doix  anderson rg goldstein jl brown ms  a mutation that impairs the ability of lipoprotein receptors to localise in coated pits on the cell surface of human fibroblasts nature   – pmid  doia  anderson rg 